Tech-legal issues are more topical than ever. Over the past year, several major scandals involving data hit the mainstream, notably the Cambridge Analytica-Facebook debacle. The already fervent interest in greater regulation of digital technologies hit an apex with the entry into force of the European Commissionâ€™s monumental General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), a path-breaking piece of legislation that will shape technology design and compliance for decades to come, and which rightly garnered the bulk of attention in our 2018 CLaw workshop.